18 Section 2. Section 25-10-711, MCA, is amended to read:
19 "25-10-711. Award of costs against governmental entity when suit or defense is frivolous or
20 pursued in bad faith. (1) In any civil action brought by or against the state, a political subdivision, or an agency
21 of the state or a political subdivision, the opposing party, whether plaintiff or defendant, is entitled to the costs
22 enumerated in 25-10-201 and reasonable attorney fees as determined by the court if:
23 (a) the opposing party prevails against the state, political subdivision, or agency; and
24 (b) the court finds that the claim or defense of the state, political subdivision, or agency that
25 brought or defended the action was frivolous or pursued in bad faith.
26 (2) Costs may be granted pursuant to subsection (1) notwithstanding any other provision of the law
27 to the contrary. The award of costs must be reasonable and considered under [section 1]."
